From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@example.com>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: Add hrtick_enabled_fair() guard in hrtick_start_fair()

hrtick_start_fair() can be called without a prior hrtick_enabled_fair()
check. Commit 95a0155224a6 ("sched/fair: Limit hrtick work") adds such
an unguarded call in task_tick_fair's queued path. This is the same
anti-pattern as the original DL bug fixed by d16b7eb6f523.

Add the hrtick_enabled_fair() check directly inside hrtick_start_fair()
to prevent the hrtick timer from being armed when HRTICK is disabled.

Fixes: 95a0155224a6 ("sched/fair: Limit hrtick work")
Signed-off-by: kSTEP <kstep@example.com>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index 3eaeceda71b0..5669b237e759 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -6744,6 +6744,9 @@ static void hrtick_start_fair(struct rq *rq, struct task_struct *p)
 
 WARN_ON_ONCE(task_rq(p) != rq);
 
+if (!hrtick_enabled_fair(rq))
+return;
+
 if (rq->cfs.h_nr_queued > 1) {
 u64 ran = se->sum_exec_runtime - se->prev_sum_exec_runtime;
 u64 slice = se->slice;
-- 
2.43.0
